description._content: Description: On the 2,200-ft. incline to Godar Landor. Mr. Jacks and Sir Harry Brittain testing the gradient. Location: Godar Landor, Persia Description: At the top of the 2,200-ft. incline on the way to Godar Landor. The figures are (left to right) Mr. T. L. Jacks (Resident Director). Sir Harry Brittain, M.P., and Mr. J. L. Wright (Fields Manager). Location: Godar Landor, Persia Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
